Wrote findings to `LCP-Vibe-1/pattern_evaluation.log`.

Key points:
- Detected only DTO-style models; no Strategy/Factory/Repository/Observer patterns.
- 42 concrete POCO classes, 0 interfaces/abstracts; 1 enum.
- Pattern density: 1 pattern type / 42 classes = 0.024.
- SOLID/decoupling grade: D — endpoints tightly coupled to concrete models; no DI abstractions or separations for testing/extensibility.

Natural next steps:
1) Introduce interfaces/abstractions for services and repositories to support DI and testing.
2) Move route handlers into controllers/services to separate transport from domain logic.
3) Add validation and domain behavior to reduce anemic-model risk.
